description.narrative: With support from UNICEF, across the sectors of maternal child health (MCH), nutrition, and WASH, around 48,466 frontline workers were trained through face-to-face training. Online training on COVID-19 prevention and control reached 637,850 views of healthcare workers. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, and considering the need on the ground, UNICEF supported the design and delivery of online training packages.; These online tools were not only used by healthcare worker across China to enhance knowledge and skills related to COVID, but also widely shared across countries in the region, and adapted for use especially at the early stages of the pandemic. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/02/2021
